{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Grease Varoma dish and set aside.","Place Parmesan cheese, onion, 1 of the garlic cloves and parsley into mixing bowl and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add breadcrumbs, beef mince, eggs, pepper and 1 tsp of the salt and knead <b>1 min\/<b>. Transfer mixture onto a sheet of baking paper (40 cm x 40 cm) and spread out to create a rectangular shape (approx. 25 cm x 20 cm, 1 cm thick). Arrange Gruyère cheese and baby spinach evenly over the meat.","Roll up meat with aid of baking paper to create a loaf shape. Remove baking paper and place meatloaf into greased Varoma dish.","Place oil, ½-1 garlic cloves, capsicum and basil into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 5<b>, then sauté <b>3 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add chopped tomatoes, water, remaining 1 tsp salt and sugar (optional), place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and cook <b>40 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>.","Set Varoma aside and allow meatloaf to cool for 5 minutes. Meanwhile, <strong>insert measuring cup<\/strong> and blend sauce <b>40 sec\/speed 8<b>. Carefully remove meatloaf from Varoma, cut into slices and serve with sauce."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["20 g extra virgin olive oil, plus extra for greasing","50 g Parmesan cheese, crust removed and cut into pieces (3 cm)","50 g brown onions, cut into halves","1 ½ - 2 garlic cloves, to taste","4 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","40 g breadcrumbs","400 g beef mince","2 eggs","½ tsp freshly ground black pepper","2 tsp salt","50 g Gruyère cheese, cut into slices (2-3 mm)","25 g fresh baby spinach leaves","450 g yellow capsicum, cut into pieces (3-4 cm)","4 - 5 fresh basil, leaves only","400 g chopped tomatoes, canned or fresh cut into pieces (2-3 cm)","200 g water","1 pinch sugar              (optional)"]}],"id":"r156334","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-vC7tpRcPsDg\/XZQwxypi-iI\/AAAAAAAAco4\/jTkHGs-druEQW6lHRJ077QbeRgkDbR-AwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_exhhJXqcccSWnXi6.png","title":"Spinach and cheese-filled meatloaf","publishedAt":"2017-05-08T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"35 g","fat":"31 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"18 g","calories":"2128 kJ \/ 508 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper","hintsAndTricks":["<i>Now this is not your ordinary meatloaf. Carefully rolled around a Gruyère-spinach filling, gently steamed to preserve a tender and moist interior and served with a fruity tomato and yellow capsicum sauce, it’s excellent both hot and cold. Great for a lunchbox or a picnic, this meatloaf can also be served at an elegant luncheon or a family supper.<\/i>","Gruyère cheese can be replaced with other cheeses (e.g. scamorza, Gouda).<br>- For an easy side dish, in <b>step 6<b> steam up to <b>400 g vegetables<b> (e.g. carrots, potatoes, green beans, courgettes, broccoli), cut in bite-size pieces, in simmering basket. Remove simmering basket when the vegetables are cooked to your liking."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","1h 15m","4 portions"]}